{
  "stem": "13469.5",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And if you didn't get it to 4,174, we had to stay there whilst they went around again, to check it all again, to see where they'd missed somebody.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Some people were out on duties outside the camp.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "There was an SS man-- the only SS man that we ever remember-- called [?",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Roy ?] [?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "Muller, ?] Red [?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "Muller-- ?] because he had red hair-- so that was why we remember this SS chap.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And he was in charge of the sewers and the ditches and the drainage.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And he had a number of Jews with them who helped him.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And they would go out, early the morning, before the appel.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "So they had to check out how many had gone with Red [?",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "Muller ?] to check the drains.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And-- and all these people had to be counted, and the count had to be matched right, according to the figure that the SS said.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Why they did the counting, nobody really knows.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But that was-- that was a habit which apparently they had in most of the camps, that everybody was counted in the morning.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Maybe to check that nobody had escaped, but in our camp, nobody ever escaped.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You know, never-- they never thought about escaping-- it was far too difficult and risky, because we all thought we were going to be exchanged anyway.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So why risk escaping?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So nobody escaped.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But very often, they didn't get the count right.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So had to stand there, and-- and we stood there for hours and hours-- five, six hours, all day, sometimes.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And-- not only in the sun, because we were in Belsen for more than a year-- from first of February '44, until April '45.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So more than a year in Belsen.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
